---
alwaysApply: true
---
Use pnpm for all commands (`pnpm install`, `pnpm run dev`, `pnpm run build`, etc.).

The main tech stack is Next.js 16 + shadcn/ui + Tailwind CSS v4.

Try to use `-primary`, `-background`, or other theme Tailwind colors over hardcoded `-[#hexcode]` values.

Try to make the main part of the component use the default font size to keep the design consistent by looking around.

If the user asks you to help with git, always look around before taking any actions so you are doing it on the right branch and can be sure the user won't need to resolve conflicts. For example, `git stash`, sync, `git stash pop` would often make it easier than pull from remote and merge, even if the edits are the same. Help the user avoid losing work by telling them the consequences of the actions you are taking.
